        </ul></p>

        <p>Since the rate of change (or slope) is consistent, the data does have a linear relationship. The linear equation looks like <m>y=-2x+b\text{.}</m></p>

        <p>The challenge is that we don't see the starting value (<m>y</m>-intercept) in the table, which is the <m>y</m> value when <m>x=0\text{.}</m> Fortunately, once we find the rate of change, we can go backward from the first row, <m>(3,-2)\text{,}</m> and figure out the starting value:</p>

